#. <section class="sutta" id="sn11.10"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn11.10:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 11"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 11"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn11.10:0.2"
msgid "1. Paṭhamavagga"
msgstr "1. The First Chapter"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 10. Samuddakasutta → isayosamuddakasuttaṃ (bj) | isayo samuddakā (sambara) (pts1)
msgctxt "sn11.10:0.3"
msgid "10. Samuddakasutta"
msgstr "10. Hermits by the Ocean"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.489"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn11.10:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthiyaṃ."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn11.10:1.2"
msgid ""
"“Bhūtapubbaṃ, bhikkhave, sambahulā isayo sīlavanto kalyāṇadhammā samuddatīre "
"paṇṇakuṭīsu sammanti."
msgstr ""
"“Once upon a time, mendicants, several hermits who were ethical, of good "
"character, settled in leaf huts by the ocean."

msgctxt "sn11.10:1.3"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena devāsurasaṅgāmo samupabyūḷho ahosi."
msgstr "Now at that time a battle was fought between the gods and the demons."

msgctxt "sn11.10:1.4"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhikkhave, tesaṃ isīnaṃ sīlavantānaṃ kalyāṇadhammānaṃ etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then the hermits thought:"

msgctxt "sn11.10:1.5"
msgid "‘dhammikā kho devā, adhammikā asurā."
msgstr "‘The gods are principled, the demons are unprincipled."

msgctxt "sn11.10:1.6"
msgid "Siyāpi no asurato bhayaṃ."
msgstr "We may be at risk from the demons."

msgctxt "sn11.10:1.7"
msgid ""
"Yannūna mayaṃ sambaraṃ asurindaṃ upasaṅkamitvā abhayadakkhiṇaṃ yāceyyāmā’ti."
msgstr ""
"Why don’t we approach Sambara, lord of demons, and beg him for a pledge of "
"safety.’"

msgctxt "sn11.10:1.8"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhikkhave, te isayo sīlavanto kalyāṇadhammā—seyyathāpi nāma balavā "
"puriso samiñjitaṃ vā bāhaṃ pasāreyya, pasāritaṃ vā bāhaṃ samiñjeyya; evameva—"
"samuddatīre paṇṇakuṭīsu antarahitā sambarassa asurindassa sammukhe "
"pāturahesuṃ."
msgstr ""
"Then, as easily as a strong person would extend or contract their arm, those "
"hermits vanished from those leaf huts by the ocean and reappeared in Sambara’"
"s presence."

msgctxt "sn11.10:1.9"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhikkhave, te isayo sīlavanto kalyāṇadhammā sambaraṃ asurindaṃ "
"gāthāya ajjhabhāsiṃsu:"
msgstr "Then those hermits addressed Sambara in verse:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn11.10:2.1"
msgid "‘Isayo sambaraṃ pattā,"
msgstr "‘The hermits have come to Sambara"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.10:2.2"
msgid "yācanti abhayadakkhiṇaṃ;"
msgstr "to beg for a pledge of safety."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.10:2.3"
msgid "Kāmaṅkaro hi te dātuṃ,"
msgstr "For you can give them what you wish,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.10:2.4"
msgid "bhayassa abhayassa vā’ti."
msgstr "whether danger or safety.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn11.10:3.1"
msgid "‘Isīnaṃ abhayaṃ natthi,"
msgstr "‘There is no safety for hermits,"

# I don’t think “devotees” of sakka is right, if anything he is their devotee!
#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.10:3.2"
msgid "duṭṭhānaṃ sakkasevinaṃ;"
msgstr "the hated associates of Sakka!"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.10:3.3"
msgid "Abhayaṃ yācamānānaṃ,"
msgstr "Though you beg me for your safety,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.10:3.4"
msgid "bhayameva dadāmi vo’ti."
msgstr "I’ll only give you fear!’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn11.10:4.1"
msgid "‘Abhayaṃ yācamānānaṃ,"
msgstr "‘Though we beg you for our safety,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.10:4.2"
msgid "bhayameva dadāsi no;"
msgstr "you give us only fear."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.10:4.3"
msgid "Paṭiggaṇhāma te etaṃ,"
msgstr "This is what we get from you:"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.10:4.4"
msgid "akkhayaṃ hotu te bhayaṃ."
msgstr "may endless peril come to you!"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn11.10:5.1"
msgid "Yādisaṃ vapate bījaṃ,"
msgstr "Whatever kind of seed you sow,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.10:5.2"
msgid "tādisaṃ harate phalaṃ;"
msgstr "that is the fruit you reap."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.10:5.3"
msgid "Kalyāṇakārī kalyāṇaṃ,"
msgstr "A doer of good gets good,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.10:5.4"
msgid "pāpakārī ca pāpakaṃ;"
msgstr "a doer of bad gets bad."

# tāta is odd here. I wonder if it’s used like a passive-aggressive “dude “or” mate”.
#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.10:5.5"
msgid "Pavuttaṃ tāta te bījaṃ,"
msgstr "You have sown your own seed, friend,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.10:5.6"
msgid "phalaṃ paccanubhossasī’ti."
msgstr "now you’ll experience the fruit.’"

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="pts1ed" id="pts1ed1.228"></a>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.491"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn11.10:6.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhikkhave, te isayo sīlavanto kalyāṇadhammā sambaraṃ asurindaṃ "
"abhisapitvā—seyyathāpi nāma balavā puriso samiñjitaṃ vā bāhaṃ pasāreyya, "
"pasāritaṃ vā bāhaṃ samiñjeyya; evameva—sambarassa asurindassa sammukhe "
"antarahitā samuddatīre paṇṇakuṭīsu pāturahesuṃ."
msgstr ""
"Then those hermits, having cursed Sambara, as easily as a strong person "
"would extend or contract their arm, vanished from Sambara’s presence and "
"reappeared in those leaf huts by the ocean."

msgctxt "sn11.10:6.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhikkhave, sambaro asurindo tehi isīhi sīlavantehi kalyāṇadhammehi "
"abhisapito rattiyā sudaṃ tikkhattuṃ ubbijjī”ti."
msgstr ""
"But after being cursed by the hermits, Sambara woke in alarm three times "
"that night.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn11.10:6.3"
msgid "Paṭhamo vaggo."
msgstr ""

#. </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "sn11.10:7.1"
msgid "Suvīraṃ susīmañceva,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.10:7.2"
msgid "dhajaggaṃ vepacittino;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.10:7.3"
msgid "Subhāsitaṃ jayañceva,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.10:7.4"
msgid "kulāvakaṃ nadubbhiyaṃ;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.10:7.5"
msgid "Verocana asurindo,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.10:7.6"
msgid "isayo araññakañceva;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.10:7.7"
msgid "Isayo ca samuddakāti."
msgstr ""
